justification: The data clump identified by key 58 represents parameters (x, y, w, h) that define the position and size of a UI element. This group of parameters is a common concept across various methods and classes that deal with layout and rendering. It occurs very often in graphical user interface code, leading to significant duplication of these parameters across different methods and classes. Refactoring this data clump into a single object would centralize the concept of a 'rectangle' or 'bounds' and reduce the duplication of these parameters throughout the codebase.
